## ðŸ’‰ Dependency Injection

```python
from tachyon_api import injectable, Depends

@injectable
class UserService:
    def get_user(self, id: str):
        return {"id": id}

@app.get("/users/{id}")
def get_user(id: str, service: UserService = Depends()):
    return service.get_user(id)
```

ðŸ‘‰ [Full DI documentation](./docs/03-dependency-injection.md)

---

## ðŸ” Security

```python
from tachyon_api.security import HTTPBearer, OAuth2PasswordBearer

bearer = HTTPBearer()

@app.get("/protected")
async def protected(credentials = Depends(bearer)):
    return {"token": credentials.credentials}
```

ðŸ‘‰ [Full Security documentation](./docs/06-security.md)

---

## âš¡ Background Tasks

```python
from tachyon_api.background import BackgroundTasks

@app.post("/notify")
def notify(background_tasks: BackgroundTasks):
    background_tasks.add_task(send_email, "user@example.com")
    return {"status": "queued"}
```

ðŸ‘‰ [Full Background Tasks documentation](./docs/09-background-tasks.md)

---

## ðŸŒ WebSockets

```python
@app.websocket("/ws")
async def websocket(ws):
    await ws.accept()
    data = await ws.receive_text()
    await ws.send_text(f"Echo: {data}")
```

ðŸ‘‰ [Full WebSockets documentation](./docs/10-websockets.md)

